{
  "texts": [
    "Then the total scaling of integrand is η -1/2-ν which is superficially IR divergent for ν ≥ 1/2.",
    "However, since we are computing wavefunction coefficients, the vertex integrals behave slightly differently from the naive expectation using field operators, thanks to the vanishing boundary condition satisfied by the bulk-bulk propagator of the exchanged field which is given byG σ (η 1, η 2, k) = -2iP σ (η 0, k) K σ (η ′, k) Im K σ (η, k)θ(η -η ′) + (η ↔ η ′).",
    "(5.61)At late times the scaling of the propagator is dictated by 18 which enjoys a softer IR scaling than σ:P 1/2 σ Im K σ,P 1/2 σ (η 0, k) Im K σ (η, k) ∼ (-η 0) 3/2+ν 1 - η η 0 + • • •, η, η 0 → 0 -.",
    "(5.62)Therefore, the actual integrand scales as (-η 0) -1/2+ν assuming that the linear-mixing vertex is later than the quartic vertex.",
    "This contribution to the wavefunction therefore remains convergent as η 0 → 0 for the whole range of light masses."
  ]
}